description:
## Problem

Query functions return full `Issue` objects, but callers often just need IDs or short hashes. This leads to repetitive mapping code throughout the codebase:

```rust
// Common patterns
let ready_ids: Vec<String> = executor.query_ready()?.iter()
    .map(|i| i.id.clone())
    .collect();

let ready_short: Vec<String> = executor.query_ready()?.iter()
    .map(|i| i.id[..8].to_string())
    .collect();
```

**Minor inconvenience but adds up:**
- Repetitive boilerplate in CLI code
- Allocates full Issue structs when only ID needed
- Less readable (ceremony obscures intent)

## Proposed API

Add convenience methods to `CommandExecutor`:

```rust
impl<S: IssueStore> CommandExecutor<S> {
    /// Get IDs of ready issues (unassigned, state=ready, unblocked)
    pub fn query_ready_ids(&self) -> Result<Vec<String>> {
        let issues = self.storage.list_issues()?;
        let resolved = build_issue_map(&issues);

        Ok(issues.iter()
            .filter(|i| i.state == State::Ready && i.assignee.is_none() && !i.is_blocked(&resolved))
            .map(|i| i.id.clone())
            .collect())
    }

    /// Get short hashes (first 8 chars) of ready issues
    pub fn query_ready_short_hashes(&self) -> Result<Vec<String>> {
        Ok(self.query_ready_ids()?
            .iter()
            .map(|id| id[..8].to_string())
            .collect())
    }

    // Similar for other common queries
    pub fn query_blocked_ids(&self) -> Result<Vec<String>> { ... }
    pub fn query_by_state_ids(&self, state: State) -> Result<Vec<String>> { ... }
    pub fn query_by_label_ids(&self, pattern: &str) -> Result<Vec<String>> { ... }
}
```

## Alternative: Generic Helper

Or add a generic helper:

```rust
pub fn extract_ids(issues: &[Issue]) -> Vec<String> {
    issues.iter().map(|i| i.id.clone()).collect()
}

pub fn extract_short_hashes(issues: &[Issue]) -> Vec<String> {
    issues.iter().map(|i| i.id[..8].to_string()).collect()
}

// Usage
let ids = extract_ids(&executor.query_ready()?);
```

## Benefits

- Less boilerplate in calling code
- More readable (intent is clearer)
- Potentially more efficient (don't clone full Issues)
- Consistent API across query methods

## Drawbacks

- Adds more methods to API surface
- Could encourage returning IDs when full Issues would be better
- May not be worth the complexity

## Decision Needed

1. Add dedicated `*_ids()` methods? (More methods but clearer)
2. Add generic helpers? (Fewer methods but requires import)
3. Do nothing? (Maybe boilerplate is acceptable)

## Acceptance Criteria (if proceeding)

- [ ] Decide on approach (dedicated methods vs helpers)
- [ ] Implement chosen approach
- [ ] Add tests for new methods/helpers
- [ ] Update CLI code to use new convenience methods where applicable
- [ ] Document usage in examples
- [ ] All existing tests pass
